// PseudoSearch
// Full-screen overlay search UI for pseudo-files; debounces API queries and supports keyboard navigation through results.
// synced: 2026-03-26T00:00:00Z

Internal type FlatResult: joins SearchResult file context with a single SearchMatch and a globalIndex for keyboard tracking.
Renders null when isOpen is false.
Results are capped at 8 files; each file shows at most 3 matches.

FUNCTION PseudoSearch(project, isOpen, onClose, onNavigate) -> JSX.Element | null [2026-03-26]                EXPORT
  CALLS: searchPseudo (pseudo-api)
  Manages query, results, highlightedIndex, loading state and refs for the overlay div, input, and debounce timer.
  flatResults memo: flattens SearchResult[] into FlatResult[], assigning sequential globalIndex values (max 3 matches per file, max 8 files).
  On query change, clears any existing debounce timer and schedules performSearch after 200ms.
  On open (isOpen true), focuses the input element.
  Registers a mousedown listener: if the click target is the overlay background element itself, calls onClose.
  Keyboard handling: Escape → onClose; ArrowDown/Up → move highlightedIndex; Enter → call onNavigate with the selected item's fileStem and functionName, then onClose.
  Renders a fixed overlay with a centered search box: text input at top, then a scrollable results list grouped visually by file stem, function name, and matching line (truncated to 80 chars). Highlighted result receives bg-purple-50.

---

FUNCTION getFileStem(filename) -> string
  Strips ".pseudo" suffix from a filename. RETURN the bare stem.

---

FUNCTION truncateLine(line, maxLen) -> string
  IF line length exceeds maxLen (default 60), RETURN the first maxLen characters followed by "...". ELSE RETURN the line unchanged.

---

FUNCTION performSearch(searchQuery) -> void
  CALLS: searchPseudo (pseudo-api)
  IF query is blank, clears results and resets highlightedIndex. ELSE sets loading, calls searchPseudo, then stores results and resets highlightedIndex on success; clears results on error.
